.TH KEEP-WEB 8 "@DATE@" "keep @VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
keep\-web \- always-on FROST co-signer and web admin for Keep
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B keep\-web
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B keep\-web
runs as a system service holding one share of a Keep FROST threshold key. It
coordinates signatures with the other shareholders over Nostr relays, so a
signature needs a quorum of devices and no single machine can sign on its own.
It also answers NIP-46 bunker requests and serves a web admin interface for
approving signing requests.
.PP
It takes no command line arguments; all configuration is read from the
environment, which the packaged systemd unit loads from
.IR /etc/keep-web/keep-web.env .
.PP
Signing is fail-closed. Requests wait for approval in the admin interface
unless
.B KEEP_FROST_AUTO_APPROVE
is set to \fBtrue\fR, and a kill switch in the admin interface disables
co-signing without stopping the service.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KEEP_PASSWORD_FILE
Path to a file holding the vault password. Required. The daemon warns if the
file is group or world accessible.
.TP
.B KEEP_PASSWORD
Vault password read directly from the environment. Discouraged: it leaks
through /proc and crash dumps. Use \fBKEEP_PASSWORD_FILE\fR.
.TP
.B KEEP_WEB_AUTH_TOKEN_FILE
Path to a file holding the bearer token that gates the admin API, including
share export. The package generates
.I /etc/keep-web/auth-token
on install and points this at it. If neither this nor
.B KEEP_WEB_AUTH_TOKEN
is set, the daemon persists a generated token to
.I $KEEP_PATH/auth_token
instead. The package pins the
.I /etc/keep-web
copy so the credential is not inside the vault directory, which is what
filesystem backups and volume snapshots capture.
.TP
.B KEEP_PATH
Vault directory. The packaged default is
.IR /var/lib/keep-web/vault ,
created on first start.
.TP
.B KEEP_WEB_LISTEN
Listen address. The packaged default is \fB127.0.0.1:8080\fR.
.TP
.B KEEP_WEB_UI_DIR
Directory holding the admin interface. The packaged default is
.IR /usr/share/keep-web/ui .
.TP
.B KEEP_BUNKER_RELAY
Comma-separated Nostr relays for the NIP-46 bunker connection.
.TP
.B KEEP_FROST_GROUP
The FROST group npub this node co-signs for.
.TP
.B KEEP_FROST_AUTO_APPROVE
Set to \fBtrue\fR to sign without per-request approval. Defaults to false.
.TP
.B KEEP_STATE_RELAY
Relay used to replicate signing state across a cluster of co-signers.
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Log filter. Defaults to \fBinfo\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/keep-web/keep-web.env
Service configuration. A conffile: local edits survive upgrades.
.TP
.I /etc/keep-web/password
Vault password. Not shipped by the package; create it with mode 0600, owned
keep\-web:keep\-web, before writing the password into it. The service fails to
start until it exists.
.TP
.I /etc/keep-web/auth-token
Bearer token for the admin API, generated on install, mode 0600
keep\-web:keep\-web. Both secrets sit in a 0750 root:keep\-web directory, so
only root and the daemon can reach them.
.TP
.I /var/lib/keep-web/vault
Encrypted vault holding the FROST share.
.SH REACHING THE ADMIN INTERFACE
The interface listens on
.B 127.0.0.1:8080
and is deliberately not reachable from the network: it grants control over
signing and can export the share. To use it from another machine, forward the
port over SSH:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ssh \-L 8080:127.0.0.1:8080 \fIuser\fR@\fIhost\fR
.EE
.RE
.PP
then browse to
.B http://127.0.0.1:8080
and sign in with the token from
.IR /etc/keep-web/auth-token .
For a permanent deployment, front it with a reverse proxy or an onion service
rather than widening
.BR KEEP_WEB_LISTEN .
.SH NOTES
The admin interface grants control over signing and must not be exposed
directly to the network. Front it with a reverse proxy or an onion service.
.PP
Purging the package removes the password and token under
.IR /etc/keep-web ,
but deliberately leaves the vault in
.IR /var/lib/keep-web :
it is the only copy of the FROST share, and deleting it would be
irrecoverable. Without the password beside it the vault is inert ciphertext.
The
.B keep\-web
account is kept for the same reason, so that nothing else inherits ownership
of the vault by reusing its uid.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR keep (1),
.BR systemd.exec (5)
.SH SECURITY
Report vulnerabilities to security@privkey.io.
